<font color="#FF0000">SNOOPY FLIGHT !ST CAV 3RD BDE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jun 14 17:09:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
     I sure would like to hear from anyone who has every served in Snoopy flight of the 3rd Bde of the 1st Cav.  I don't know how long the flight was active but I was a crewchief in1970-71.  <br>
     I know that it was at least a couple of years old when I got there.  We flew command and control and the 5 LOHs we had flew scout with the 20th Air Arty.<br>
     I am most interested in hearing from any and all doorgunners and crewchiefs of the UH-1, D and H models.<br>
Any and all doorgunners are welcome to e-mail me at anytime.  I teach school and I use some of my experiences for teaching Vietnam.  It would be nice to incorporate other veterans stories.<br>
     I know a number of skytroopers from my time in Vietnam but I only get to talk with one of them, every now and then.  I would like to hear more.<br>
     Waiting to hear from Snoopy Flight platoon members.    <br>

